Phase 6: Monitoring & Validation






Add an endpoint to monitor pool performance:




1. ⚠️ CRITICAL: Enable Concurrent Socket Factory Use
You must explicitly enable concurrent socket creation for FastestConnectServerSet to work.  Without this, the code will throw an exception because it tries to connect to all 8 servers simultaneously. 

Add this line to your LDAPConnectionOptions:
options.setAllowConcurrentSocketFactoryUse(true); // REQUIRED for FastestConnectServerSet   



2. ⚠️ CRITICAL: Health Check Limitation in Thread-Local Pools
LDAPThreadLocalConnectionPool does NOT support background health checks (unlike the standard LDAPConnectionPool).  It only checks health when a connection is created or checked out.

Risk: If a server dies while a thread is idle, the thread won't know until its next request. 
Fix: You must rely on fast timeouts and exception handling rather than proactive background monitoring. 
Adjustment: Remove setHealthCheckIntervalMillis from your pool config (it will be ignored) and ensure your connectTimeout is aggressive (500ms). 



3. ⚠️ CRITICAL: Thread Pool Sizing Mismatch
If you use a standard Spring Boot web server (Tomcat/Jetty), the default thread pool is ~200.

Math: 200 threads × 5 min connections = 1,000 simultaneous LDAP connections.
Risk: Your LDAP servers (or firewall) might reject 1,000 concurrent SSL handshakes. 
Fix: Tune your Tomcat thread pool (server.tomcat.threads.max) to match your LDAP capacity, OR reduce the minConnections per thread in your LDAP pool to 1. 



